        "id": 12702,
        "name": "Oleg Samarin",
        "username": "osamarin",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/osamarin/{size}/905_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-04-10T14:09:53.416Z",
        "cooked": "<p>FDB allows to query by a key or a key range, <code>uuid</code> in your case. So if you need to query by a part of value efficiently, you have create secondary key-value pairs: {name+uuid, }. Then you will be able to query by name using the range with the prefix <code>name</code> and to get a list of <code>uuid</code>s of the students with given name, then, to query their data by uuid.</p>\n<p>You can use the <code>Record Layer</code> on top of fdb, that does a part of this work automatically. There is a special part <a href=\"https://forums.foundationdb.org/c/using-layers\">Using Layers</a> in this community forum.</p>",
